CSS BOX Model - Margin, padding and border

The concept box model has
- Margin
- Padding
- Border
- height
- weight

concepts

what is it ?
each element is a box in itself, we can change the dimensions of these boxes
and decide how they are laid out on the screen.

we can use pixels or percentages to change the size of the box,
the box moves the other elements.

border can take three values seperated with space
border : 10px(thickness of the border) solid(style of the border) black(color of the border);

these are the three items that together determine what the border looks like

the height and width of the box does not change when we change the border,
the border goes outwards

we can provide more specific rules

border : 30px solid black;
    border-top: 0px;


this border width works similarly as the border property works

              1    2    3    4
border-width: 0px 10px 20px 30px;


                  1
        --------------------
        |                   |
        |                   |
4       |                   |       2
        |                   |
        |                   |
        ---------------------
                  3

it goes in clockwise
we can also give two values to the border-width property

{
    border-width : 20px 10px
}

it would then set 1+3 and 2+4


## Padding
Imagine a box is a paragraph element
and has a border property, if we have a padding added, it would push the
border outside, the height and the width of the box does not change, but increases space
between the box and the border

## Margin
margin is outside of the border and other content


padding and margin similar to border and border-width function in a similar way, like we can provide 4 values to them,


